Myagdi, June 27: A man has died after being hit by a tipper at the Myagdikhola Hydropower Project area in Ratakhola, Dhaulagiri Rural Municipality-4 of the district this morning.&nbsp;

According to the District Police Office, the tipper (Bap 01-004 Ka 1377) hit a worker of the project. Bhim Bahadur Sarki, 35, a resident of Laljhadi Rural Municipality-4 of Kanchanpur, was seriously injured in the accident. He was taken to the Provincial Hospital in Beni for treatment, but was declared dead upon arrival by doctors, shared Police Inspector Sagar Timilsina of the District Police Office.

The tipper driver, Rajesh Ghalan, 30, of Bhimphedi Rural Municipality-3 of Makawanpur, has been taken into custody for necessary legal action. (RSS)

description:
By Shashidhar Parajuli, Biratnagar, June 27 : The Morang District Administration Office has launched a targeted initiative to address serious cases of usurious lending (loan sharking) after an increasing number of victims were driven to suicide or rendered landless by exploitative lending practices.&nbsp;

The administration has placed 100 of the most critical complaints on a fast-track process for investigation and resolution. The move comes in response to a growing number of protests by victims and several suicide cases linked to loan sharking.&nbsp;

According to Morang Chief District Officer Yubaraj Kattel, priority is being given to cases involving individuals who are at immediate risk of taking their own lives or losing all their property and becoming landless. This gap between the executive and the judiciary makes it difficult for us to proceed."

Morang Police Chief Superintendent of Police (SP) Kabit Katuwal said strict action would be taken against those involved in exploitative lending.

